=====Usage notes=====
* This word is an [[enclitic]] just like other [[particle]]s. It is classified as {{l|ja|[[助動詞]]|tr=jodōshi}} in traditional Japanese grammar, because of its particle-like phonological behavior.
* This particle only applies to nouns and ''na''-adjectives. An ''i''-adjective or verb alone suffices to end a sentence or clause. For example, {{m|ja|美しい|tr=Utsukushii}} could mean "it's beautiful", analogous to {{m|ja|[[綺麗]]'''だ'''|tr=Kirei da|t=It's pretty.}}
** {{m|ja|です|tr=desu}} can be applied to ''i''-adjectives, while {{m|ja|だろう|tr=darō}}/{{m|ja|でしょう|tr=deshō}} and {{m|ja|なら|tr=nara}} can be applied to both ''i''-adjectives and verbs.
* Although だ cannot be used to introduce a relative clause ending in a ''na''-adjective or noun – {{m|ja|[[学生]]'''だ'''[[アリス]]}} doesn't work, nor does {{m|ja|です}} here – some of the conjugations of だ can: {{m|ja|[[学生]][[である]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who is a student), {{m|ja|[[学生]][[だった]]/[[であった]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who was a student), {{m|ja|[[学生]][[ではない]]/[[じゃない]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who is not a student), {{m|ja|[[学生]][[ではなかった]]/[[じゃなかった]][[アリス]]}} (Alice who was not a student).

